@attribute [Route("/components/" + nameof(HxPasswordStrength))]

<ApiDoc Type="typeof(HxPasswordStrength)">
	<DocHeading Title="Basic usage" />
	<p>
		Place a password input inside the component&mdash;the strength meter automatically attaches to the first
		<code>input[type="password"]</code> found in the content and re-evaluates the password on every keystroke.
		The evaluation happens entirely in JavaScript (in the browser), there are no server round-trips and the password never leaves the input.
	</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxPasswordStrength_Demo)" Tabs="false" />
	<DocAlert Type="DocAlertType.Info">
		<code>HxPasswordStrength</code> is not a form input&mdash;it only observes the password input.
		It can be freely combined with <code>EditForm</code> validation, the validation classes of the input are not affected.
	</DocAlert>

	<DocHeading Title="Progress bar" />
	<p>Use <code>Variant="PasswordStrengthVariant.ProgressBar"</code> for a single bar which grows with the password strength.</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxPasswordStrength_Demo_ProgressBar)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Text feedback" />
	<p>
		Set <code>ShowText="true"</code> to display a text message for the current strength level below the meter.
		The default messages (Weak, Fair, Good, Strong) are localized; use the <code>WeakText</code>, <code>FairText</code>,
		<code>GoodText</code>, and <code>StrongText</code> parameters to customize them.
	</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxPasswordStrength_Demo_TextFeedback)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Strength criteria" />
	<p>
		The scoring algorithm awards points for meeting the minimum length (<code>MinLength</code>, 8 characters by default),
		exceeding it by 4+ characters, containing lowercase and uppercase letters, numbers, special characters (one and multiple),
		and for 16+ characters length. Adjust the point values with the <code>Weights</code> parameter (set a weight to <code>0</code>
		to disable a criterion) and the level boundaries with the <code>Thresholds</code> parameter.
	</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxPasswordStrength_Demo_Criteria)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Strength change event" />
	<p>
		Use the <code>OnStrengthChanged</code> event to react to strength level changes.
		The event carries the new level (<code>null</code> when the password is empty) and the computed score.
	</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxPasswordStrength_Demo_StrengthChanged)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Static display" />
	<p>
		Set the <code>Strength</code> parameter to render the meter statically (CSS-only, no JavaScript evaluation),
		e.g. for a strength value computed by your own logic.
	</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxPasswordStrength_Demo_Static)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Input outside the component" />
	<p>
		When the password input cannot be placed inside the component, target it with the <code>InputSelector</code> parameter (a CSS selector).
	</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxPasswordStrength_Demo_InputSelector)" />
</ApiDoc>
